</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>You can read up on the bitcoins. &nbsp;As the usage grows so does the number but at a very slow rate due to the mining nodes guessing the right keys to ensure the transactions is not a fake bitcoin. &nbsp;Once the guess is correct, then the mining node is rewarded with bitcoins that are issued into the system.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>This is very much a deflationary design, not inflationary. &nbsp;If Ben B only issued another million dollars next year, but our population grew by 5 million, would you call the monetary policy deflationary or inflationary assuming the same velocity of course.</p>

